10-12-2025:

Adding a backup directory on all nodes: (repeat steps in all nodes)

[admin@crdb2 ~]$ sudo mkdir /var/lib/cockroachbkp
[sudo] password for admin:
[admin@crdb2 ~]$ sudo chown cockroach:cockroach /var/lib/cockroachbkp/
[admin@crdb2 ~]$

Edit the service file add make changes to ExecStart:

[admin@crdb1 ~]$ sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/cockroachdb.service


ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/cockroach start \
    --certs-dir=/var/lib/cockroach/certs  \
    --store=/var/lib/cockroach/data \
    --join=10.0.40.2 \
    --advertise-addr=10.0.40.2:26257 \
    --http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080 \
    --listen-addr=0.0.0.0:26257 \
    --cache=25% \
    --max-sql-memory=25% \
    --external-io-dir=/var/lib/cockroachbkp

[admin@crdb2 ~]$ sudo systemctl daemon-reload
[admin@crdb2 ~]$ sudo systemctl restart cockroachdb.service
[admin@crdb2 ~]$


-------------------------- backup directory configuration completed -----------------------


CREATE SCHEDULE [IF NOT EXISTS] <label>
FOR BACKUP [<targets>] INTO <location>
[WITH <backup_options>[=<value>] [, ...]]
RECURRING [crontab] [FULL BACKUP <crontab|ALWAYS>]
[WITH SCHEDULE OPTIONS <schedule_option>[= <value>] [, ...] ]

Targets:
   Empty targets list: backup full cluster.
   TABLE <table_pattern> [, ...]
   DATABASE <database_name> [, ...]

BAckup Schedules:

CREATE SCHEDULE  cluster_bkp
FOR BACKUP  INTO 'nodelocal://1/backups/cluster-full'
RECURRING 01 00  * * 1-6  FULL BACKUP 01 00 * * 0

Example:

 CREATE SCHEDULE  cluster_bkp FOR BACKUP  INTO 'nodelocal://1/backups/cluster-full'  RECURRING '@daily' FULL BACKUP '1 0 * * 0'


root@localhost:26257/defaultdb> drop schedule 1131465234631294977;
DROP SCHEDULES 1

Time: 9ms total (execution 8ms / network 0ms)

root@localhost:26257/defaultdb> show schedules;


S3 backup commands:

-- Full cluster backup
BACKUP INTO 's3://my-crdb-backups?AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxx&AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=yyyy';

-- Backup a specific database
BACKUP DATABASE mydb INTO 's3://my-crdb-backups?AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxx&AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=yyyy';

-- Backup a specific table
BACKUP TABLE mydb.mytable INTO 's3://my-crdb-backups?AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=xxxx&AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=yyyy';

11-12-25:

Upgrading from 24.3 to 25.2:

Upgrading:


root@localhost:26257/defaultdb> SET CLUSTER SETTING
                             -> diagnostics.reporting.enabled =
                             -> true;



